# AI Automation Lab

Multi-agent platform for creating, testing, and deploying AI agents with skills, memory, tools, MCP servers, sandboxed execution, and scheduled automations.

## Layout

- `backend/` — Bun + Hono + bun:sqlite API server. Source in `backend/src/`.
  - `agents/` — registry, files, runtime, permissions, history
  - `api/server.ts` — Hono routes (auth, agents, chats, skills, memory, runs, secrets, MCP, sandbox, webspace, workspace)
  - `automations/` — scheduled agent tasks + polling scheduler
  - `db/` — schema + migrations
  - `llm/` — OpenAI/Anthropic/Ollama provider abstraction
  - `sandbox/` — local sandboxed execution
  - `mcp/` — MCP client + store
  - `memory/` — per-(agent, owner) long-term memory store
  - `runs/` — run + tool invocation records
  - `skills/` — global + per-user skill registry (markdown + frontmatter)
  - `tools/` — tool registry + builtins (read/write/exec/http/memory/etc)
- `frontend/` — Vite + React + Tailwind UI. Source in `frontend/src/`.
- `docs/` — durable design notes and plans.
  - `docs/plans/` — dated architecture / implementation plans
- `data/` — agents, skills, memory, sandboxes, sqlite DB. Created at runtime.

## Run

```bash
# backend
cd backend && bun run src/main.ts

# frontend
cd frontend && bun run dev
```

Backend defaults to `:8787`; frontend to a Vite port.
